questions.question: Let the vertices of a triangle $ABC$ be $A(1, 1, 1)$, $B(2, 2, 3)$, and $C(3, 1, 2)$. If the area of the triangle is $\Delta$, find the value of $(2\Delta)^2$.

An experimental setup for measuring rotational kinetic energy is calibrated using reference standards for mass, length, and time. If the measurement of mass has an accuracy of $3\%$, length has an accuracy of $4\%$, and time has an accuracy of $2\%$, the maximum percentage error in the estimated rotational kinetic energy will be _____________.

To estimate the height of a bridge over a river, a stone is dropped freely on the river from the bridge. The stone takes $2\text{ s}$ to touch the water surface of the river. Calculate the height of the bridge from the water level. [Take $g = 9.8\text{ m/s}^2$]

A bullet is fired with an initial velocity $\vec{u} = (3\hat{i} + 4\hat{j})\text{ m/s}$ and is subjected to a constant acceleration $\vec{a} = (0.4\hat{i} + 0.3\hat{j})\text{ m/s}^2$. The speed of the bullet at the end of $10\text{ s}$ is:

A small metallic sphere of mass $100\text{ g}$ is attached to a flexible rod of length $2\text{ m}$ and rotated in a horizontal circle on a frictionless surface. If the sphere revolves at a speed of $\frac{600}{\pi}\text{ rev./min}$, calculate the tension acting on the rod.

Two masses ${m_1} = 5kg$ and ${m_2} = 4.8kg$ tied to a string are hanging over a light frictionless pulley. What is the acceleration of the masses when left free to move? $\left( {g = 9.8m/{s^2}} \right)$

In a collinear collision, a particle with an initial speed $v_{0}$ strikes a stationary particle of the same mass. If the magnitude of the relative velocity between the two particles after the collision is $\sqrt{2}v_{0}$, the ratio of the initial kinetic energy to the final total kinetic energy is:

Moment of inertia of an equilateral triangular lamina ABC, about the axis
passing through its centre O and perpendicular to its plane is I$_{o}$ as shown in the figure. A cavity DEF is cut out from the lamina, where D, E, F are the mid points of the sides. Moment of inertia of the remaining part of lamina about the same axis is :
Under isothermal conditions, the pressure of a gas is given by $P = 2V^{-3}$, where $V$ is the volume of the gas. The bulk modulus of the gas at constant temperature is equal to:

If a piece of metal is heated to temperature $\theta $ and then allowed to cool in a room which is at temperature ${\theta _0},$ the graph between the temperature $T$ of the metal and time $t$ will be closest to

Two ideal gases, $X$ (diatomic, $\gamma_1 = 7/5$) and $Y$ (monatomic, $\gamma_2 = 5/3$), are mixed together. If the adiabatic exponent of the resulting mixture is $\gamma_{\text{mix}} = 1.5$, find the ratio of the number of moles of gas $X$ to the number of moles of gas $Y$ in the mixture.
For a particular ideal gas which of the following graphs represents the variation of mean squared velocity of the gas molecules with temperature?

A vertical spring extends by $5\text{ cm}$ when a force of $10\text{ N}$ is applied to it. If a mass of $2\text{ kg}$ is attached to the spring and set into vertical oscillations, the frequency of the resulting motion is approximately:

A source of sound $S$ emitting waves of frequency $100\text{ Hz}$ and an observer $O$ are located at some distance from each other. The source is moving with a speed of $19.4\text{ m/s}$ at an angle of $60^\circ$ with the source-observer line. The observer is at rest. If the velocity of sound in air is $330\text{ m/s}$, the apparent frequency observed by the observer is:

A rod is made of a material with an absolute permeability of $2\pi \times 10^{-4}\text{ H/m}$. If the permeability of vacuum is $\mu_0 = 4\pi \times 10^{-7}\text{ H/m}$, the magnetic susceptibility ($\chi_m$) of the material is:
An ac source is connected in the given circuit. The value of $\phi$ will be :

An electromagnetic wave is propagating through vacuum along the positive $Z$-axis. Which of the following pairs could represent the directions of the electric field vector $(\vec{E})$ and the magnetic field vector ($\vec{B}$) respectively?

For a concave lens of focal length f, the relation
between object and image distances u and v,
respectively, from its pole can best be
represented by (u = v is the reference line) :

For Young's double slit experiment, two statements are given below:

$\pmb{\text{Statement I:}}$ If the screen is moved away from the plane of slits, the angular separation of the fringes remains constant.
$\pmb{\text{Statement II:}}$ If the monochromatic source is replaced by another monochromatic source of larger wavelength, the angular separation of fringes decreases.

In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below:
questions.option_a: Both Statement I and Statement II are true
questions.option_b: Both Statement I and Statement II are false
questions.option_c: Statement I is true but Statement II is false
questions.option_d: Statement I is false but Statement II is true

questions.question: In a radioactive material, the activity is measured to be $A_1$ at time $t_1$ and $A_2$ at a later time $t_2$. If the decay constant of the material is $\lambda$, the ratio of the activities $\frac{A_1}{A_2}$ is given by:

A point mass of $2\text{ kg}$ starts from rest. A constant force of $40\text{ N}$ is applied to the body for a duration of $5\text{ seconds}$. Find the kinetic energy acquired by the body at the end of this time.

A rod made of metal $X$ has a length of $1\text{ m}$ and a cross-sectional area of $10^{-4}\text{ m}^2$. The rod is heated from $0^{\circ}\text{C}$ to $200^{\circ}\text{C}$ without being allowed to extend or bend. If the compressive tension developed in the rod is $4 \times 10^{4}\text{ N}$, then the coefficient of linear expansion of metal $X$ is $\beta \times 10^{-5}\text{ K}^{-1}$. The value of $\beta$ is ________. (Given Young's modulus of metal $X = 2 \times 10^{11}\text{ Nm}^{-2}$)

A parallel plate capacitor has plate area $7\text{ m}^2$ and plate separation of $8\text{ mm}$. The space between the plates is filled up to a thickness $5\text{ mm}$ with material of dielectric constant $10$. The resultant capacitance of the system is $x\text{ nF}$. The value of $x$ to the nearest integer is ________. [$\epsilon_0 = 8.85 \times 10^{-12}\text{ F m}^{-1}$]

A magnetic field of strength $\vec{B} = (2 \hat{k})\text{ T}$ acts on a charge of $8.0 \mu\text{C}$ moving with a velocity of $8.0 \times 10^6\text{ ms}^{-1}$ along the positive $y$-axis. The force acting on the charge is $x \hat{i}\text{ N}$. The value of $x$ is ________.

The current in a coil of self-inductance $2.0\text{ H}$ is increasing according to the relation $I = 2 \sin(t^2)\text{ A}$. The amount of energy stored in the inductor during the period when the current changes from $0$ to $2\text{ A}$ is ________ $J$.

If a sample of $20~\text{mg}$ is taken for each of the following elements, which one will contain the greatest number of atoms?

Elements: $\text{Po, Pt, Pb, Pr}$

Identify the elements $A$ and $B$ based on the provided ionization energy $(\text{IE})$ values in the table below:

$$\begin{array}{|c|c|c|}
\hline
\textbf{Element} & \textbf{1}^{\text{st}} \text{ IE (kJ/mol)} & \textbf{2}^{\text{nd}} \text{ IE (kJ/mol)} \\
\hline
A & 495 & 4563 \\
\hline
B & 731 & 1450 \\
\hline
\end{array}$$

Choose the correct pair from the following options:
Which of the following chemical species is considered non-existent or unstable under standard conditions?

Match the thermodynamic processes in $\textbf{List I}$ with their corresponding descriptions in $\textbf{List II}$:

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|}
\hline
\textbf{List I (Process)} & \textbf{List II (Conditions)} \\
\hline
\text{A. Isobaric process} & \text{I. No heat exchange with surroundings} \\
\hline
\text{B. Isothermal process} & \text{II. Carried out at constant pressure} \\
\hline
\text{C. Adiabatic process} & \text{III. Carried out at constant volume} \\
\hline
\text{D. Isochoric process} & \text{IV. Carried out at constant temperature} \\
\hline
\end{array}$$

Choose the correct match from the options below:

A gaseous species $\text{X}$ dissociates into $\text{Y}$ and $\text{Z}$ according to the following equilibrium in a closed reaction vessel:

$$\text{X}(g) \rightleftharpoons \text{Y}(g) + \text{Z}(g)$$

If the total pressure at equilibrium is $P$ and the degree of dissociation of $\text{X}$ is $0.4$, the partial pressure of $\text{Y}$ will be:

A $0.050~\text{mol L}^{-1}$ solution of a monobasic weak acid exhibits a molar conductivity $(\Lambda_m)$ of $100~\text{S cm}^2 \text{mol}^{-1}$. Determine the degree of dissociation $(\alpha)$ for the acid given the following limiting molar conductivities: $\Lambda_{+}^{\circ} = 441~\text{S cm}^2 \text{mol}^{-1}$ and $\Lambda_{-}^{\circ} = 59~\text{S cm}^2 \text{mol}^{-1}$.

A $50~\text{mL}$ sample of $0.2~\text{M}$ ammonia solution is mixed with $25~\text{mL}$ of $0.2~\text{M}$ hydrochloric acid. If the $\text{p}K_b$ of ammonia is $4.75$, what is the $\text{pOH}$ of the resulting mixture?
Identify the process in which the change in the oxidation state is five:
Which of the following reactions is a part of the large-scale industrial preparation of nitric acid?

Match the chemical structures in $\textbf{List-I}$ with their corresponding $\textbf{IUPAC}$ names in $\textbf{List-II}$:

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|}
\hline
\textbf{List-I (Structure)} & \textbf{List-II (IUPAC Name)} \\
\hline
A. \text{ } \text{CH}_3\text{CH}_2\text{CH(C}_2\text{H}_5\text{)CH}_2\text{CH(CH}_3\text{)CH}_2\text{CH}_3 & 1. \text{ 4-Methylpent-1-ene} \\

B. \text{ (CH}_3\text{)}_2\text{C(C}_3\text{H}_7\text{)}_2 & 2. \text{ 3-Ethyl-5-methylheptane} \\

D. \text{ (CH}_3\text{)}_2\text{CHCH}_2\text{CH=CH}_2 & 4. \text{ 2-Methyl-1,3-pentadiene} \\

Choose the correct match from the options provided below:

Arrange the following carbanions in order of their decreasing stability:

$$(CH_3)_3\text{C}^-, \quad \text{Cl}_3\text{C}^-, \quad (CH_3)_2\text{CH}^-, \quad \text{C}_6\text{H}_5\text{CH}_2^-$$

Compound $\textbf{A}$ formed in the following reaction reacts with $\textbf{B}$ to give the product $\textbf{(C)}$. Find out $\textbf{A}$ and $\textbf{B}$.

$$\text{CH}_3-\text{C}\equiv\text{CH} + \text{Na} \longrightarrow \pmb{\text{A}} \xrightarrow{\pmb{\text{B}}} \text{CH}_3-\text{C}\equiv\text{C}-\text{CH}_2-\text{CH}_2-\text{CH}_3 \quad \pmb{\text{(C)}} + \text{NaBr}$$
The vapour pressure of a dilute aqueous solution of glucose is $750~\text{mm}$ of $\text{Hg}$ at $373~\text{K}$. Calculate the mole fraction of the solute in this solution.

Azomethane $(CH_3N_2CH_3)$ decomposes into ethane and nitrogen gas according to the following chemical equation:

$$CH_3N_2CH_3(g) \rightarrow C_2H_6(g) + N_2(g)$$

The initial concentration of azomethane was $1.50 \times 10^{-2}~\text{mol L}^{-1}$. After $10$ minutes, the concentration decreased to $1.29 \times 10^{-2}~\text{mol L}^{-1}$. The average rate of reaction during this time interval is:
(image) An alcohol of formula $C_9H_{12}O$ reacts with $Na_2Cr_2O_7$ to form a compound having formula $C_9H_{10}O$. The original alcohol might be:

Identify (A) in the following reaction sequence :

$\textbf{Statement I:}$ D-(+)-glucose + D-(+) fructose $\xrightarrow{-\text{H}_2 \text{O}}$ Sucrose
$$\text{sucrose} \xrightarrow{\text{hydrolysis}} \text{D-(+)-glucose} + \text{D-(+)-fructose}$$
$\textbf{Statement II:}$ Invert sugar is formed during sucrose hydrolysis.

In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below:

questions.question: In Lassaigne's extract of an organic compound, when both nitrogen and sulphur are present, a blood red colour is observed upon addition of $Fe^{3+}$ ions. This colouration is due to the formation of:
The total number of electrons present in the $4^{\text{th}}$ shell of Astatine $(Z=85)$ is:

A box contains $0.90~\text{g}$ of liquid water in equilibrium with water vapour at $27^\circ\text{C}$. The equilibrium vapour pressure of water at $27^\circ\text{C}$ is $32.0~\text{Torr}$. When the volume of the box is increased, some of the liquid water evaporates to maintain the equilibrium pressure. If all the liquid water evaporates, then the volume of the box must be __________ $\text{cm}^3$. [nearest integer]

[Assume water vapour behaves as an ideal gas and ignore the volume of the liquid water. Given: $R = 0.082~\text{L atm K}^{-1} \text{mol}^{-1}$]

A sample of $0.125~\text{g}$ of an organic compound, when analyzed by Dumas' method, yields $22.78~\text{mL}$ of nitrogen gas collected over $\text{KOH}$ solution at $280~\text{K}$ and $759~\text{mm Hg}$. The percentage of nitrogen in the given organic compound is __________. (Nearest integer)

[Given: Vapour pressure of water at $280~\text{K}$ is $14.2~\text{mm Hg}$; $R = 0.082~\text{L atm K}^{-1} \text{mol}^{-1}$]

For the electrochemical cell reaction occurring at $25^\circ\text{C}$:

$$Cd_{(s)} + Hg_2SO_{4(s)} + \frac{9}{5}H_2O_{(l)} \rightleftharpoons CdSO_4 \cdot \frac{9}{5}H_2O_{(s)} + 2Hg_{(l)}$$

The standard electromotive force ($E^\circ_{\text{cell}}$) is measured to be $4.315~\text{V}$. Given that the standard enthalpy change ($\Delta H^\circ$) is $-825.2~\text{kJ mol}^{-1}$ and the Faraday constant is $96487~\text{C mol}^{-1}$, calculate the value of $100\Delta S^\circ$, where $\Delta S^\circ$ is the standard entropy change in $\text{J K}^{-1} \text{mol}^{-1}$. [Round your final answer to the nearest integer]

Aniline and N-methylaniline can be distinguished by using how many of the following tests?

(I) Tollen's reagent 
(II) Hinsberg reagent 
(III) Carbylamine test 
(IV) Mulliken Test 
(V) Azo dye test 
(VI) Bayer's test 
(VII) Lucas test 
(VIII) Hofmann mustard oil test

Let $S = \mathbb{N} \cup \{0\}$ be the set of non-negative integers. A relation $R$ from $S$ to $\mathbb{R}$ is defined as:

$$R = \left\{ (x, y) : \ln y = x \ln \left( \frac{2}{5} \right), x \in S, y \in \mathbb{R} \right\}$$

If $k$ denotes the sum of all elements in the range of $R$, determine the value of $3k$.

Suppose the lines defined by $(2 - i)z = (2 + i)\overline{z}$ and $(2 + i)z + (i - 2)\overline{z} - 4i = 0$ are normals to a circle $C$ in the complex plane. If the line $iz + \overline{z} + 1 + i = 0$ is tangent to this circle, determine its circumference.

If $a, b, c$ are three non-zero real numbers such that 

$$4a^2 + 9b^2 + c^2 - 6ab - 3bc - 2ca = 0$$

then determine the value of the expression $\displaystyle \frac{4a + c}{b}$.

Consider the infinite alternating series defined by:

$$S = \frac{1}{1 \cdot 2} - \frac{1}{2 \cdot 3} + \frac{1}{3 \cdot 4} - \frac{1}{4 \cdot 5} + \dots \infty$$

Determine the value of $e^S$.

Let the centroid of an equilateral triangle ABC be at the origin. Let one of the sides of the equilateral triangle be along the straight line x + y = 3. If R and r be the radius of circumcircle and incircle respectively of $\Delta$ABC, then (R + r) is equal to :

Two parabolas are given by the equations $y^2 = 4q(x - r)$ and $y^2 = 8px$. If these curves share a common normal line that is not the $x$-axis, determine the necessary condition relating the parameters $p, q,$ and $r$.
For a certain ellipse, the distance between the two foci is $6$ and the length of the latus rectum is $3\sqrt{2}$. Determine the distance between the two directrices of this ellipse.

Let the tangent drawn to the parabola $y^2 = 24x$ at the point $(\alpha, \beta)$ be perpendicular to the line 

$$2x + 2y = 5$$

If the normal is drawn to the hyperbola $\displaystyle \frac{x^2}{\alpha^2} - \frac{y^2}{\beta^2} = 1$ at the point $(\alpha + 4, \beta + 4)$, determine the equation of this normal.
Determine the value of the following limit: $\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 0} \left( \frac{ax^2 + c}{bx^2 + c} \right)^{\frac{1}{x^2}}$, where $a = 3$, $b = 7$, and $c = 2$.

A function $y = g(x)$ is expressed as the determinant of a $3 \times 3$ matrix:

$$g(x) = \begin{vmatrix} 2 \cos^4 x & 2 \sin^4 x & 3 + \sin^2 2x \\ 3 + 2 \cos^4 x & 2 \sin^4 x & \sin^2 2x \\ 2 \cos^4 x & 3 + 2 \sin^4 x & \sin^2 2x \end{vmatrix}$$

Calculate the value of $\displaystyle \frac{1}{5} g'(e^{20})$.

Suppose five distinct colors are available to paint three different rooms. If each room is assigned exactly one color, determine the probability that the three rooms are painted using exactly two different colors.
Given $|x| < \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}$, consider the function $y = \frac{3x - x^3}{1 - 3x^2}$. Determine which of the following expressions is equivalent to $\tan^{-1} y$.

Suppose two variables $x$ and $y$ satisfy the equation $\cos^{-1} x - \cos^{-1} \left( \frac{y}{2} \right) = \theta$, where the domain constraints are $-1 \le x \le 1$, $-2 \le y \le 2$, and $x \le \frac{y}{2}$. Determine the value of the expression $4x^2 - 4xy \cos \theta + y^2$.

Let $t$ be a complex root of the quadratic equation $x^2 + x + 1 = 0$. Suppose the real constants $c_1$ and $c_2$ are uniquely determined by the matrix multiplication:

$$\begin{bmatrix} 4 & c_1 & c_2 \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} 1 & 16 & 13 \\ -1 & -1 & 2 \\ -2 & -14 & -8 \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} 0 & 0 & 0 \end{bmatrix}$$

If the real numbers $p$ and $q$ satisfy the equation $\displaystyle \frac{4}{t^4} + \frac{p}{t^{c_1}} + \frac{q}{t^{c_2}} = 3$, find the value of the product $pq$.

Suppose the constants $a$ and $b$ are defined by the limit equation $$\displaystyle \lim_{x \to \ \infty} \left( \sqrt{x^2 - x + 1} - ax \right) = b$$. Determine the minimum value of the trigonometric function $f(\theta) = a\sin\theta + b\cos\theta$.

Evaluate the limit $$\displaystyle L = \lim_{x \to \infty} \frac{(2x^2 - 3x + 5)(3x - 1)^{\frac{x}{2}}}{(3x^2 + 5x + 4)\sqrt{(3x + 2)^x}}$$. If $L$ represents this limit, determine the value of $9eL^2$.

Given the integral identity 

$$\int \frac{\sin x}{\sin(x - \phi)} \, dx = k_1 x + k_2 \ln |\sin(x - \phi)| + C$$

where $\phi$ is a constant, determine the value of the expression $k_1^2 + k_2^2$.
The area of the region bounded by y $-$ x = 2 and x$^{2}$ = y is equal to :

Consider a function $y = f(x)$ that satisfies the first-order linear differential equation 

$$(x^2 + 1) \frac{dy}{dx} - 2xy = (x^2 + 1)^2 \cos x$$

with the initial condition $y(0) = 1$. Determine the value of $y$ when $x = 1$.

Consider two vectors $\vec{u}$ and $\vec{v}$ such that $|\vec{u}| = 1$, $|\vec{v}| = 4$, and their scalar product is $\vec{u} \cdot \vec{v} = 2$. If a third vector $\vec{w}$ is defined by the relation:

$$\vec{w} = (2\vec{u} \times \vec{v}) - 3\vec{v}$$

then determine the angle between the vectors $\vec{v}$ and $\vec{w}$.

Let $g : \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}$ be a function defined by $$g(x) = \frac{2e^{2x}}{e^{2x} + e}$$If $S$ represents the sum $g\left(\frac{1}{100}\right) + g\left(\frac{2}{100}\right) + g\left(\frac{3}{100}\right) + \cdots + g\left(\frac{99}{100}\right)$, then find the value of $$\sqrt{S + 1}$$.

Consider the set of all $\beta \in \mathbb{R}$ for which the equation $\cos 2\theta + \beta \sin \theta = 2\beta - 7$ has at least one solution. If this set is the interval $[m, n]$, and $$s = \tan 9^{\circ} - \tan 27^{\circ} - \frac{1}{\cot 63^{\circ}} + \tan 81^{\circ}$$, then determine the value of $\frac{mn}{s}$.

Five-digit numbers are formed using the digits from the set $\{0, 2, 3, 4, 7, 9\}$, with repetition of digits permitted. These numbers are then arranged in ascending order and assigned consecutive serial numbers starting from 1. Determine the serial number assigned to the number 42920.

Let $$A = \{(x, y) \in \mathbb{N} \times \mathbb{N}: 9(x-3)^{2}+16(y-4)^{2} \leq 144\}$$ and $$B = \{(x, y) \in \mathbb{R} \times \mathbb{R}: (x-7)^{2}+(y-4)^{2} \leq 36\}$$Determine the value of $n(A \cap B)$, where $n$ denotes the number of elements in the set.

Consider the statistical measures for two distinct data sets as shown below:

$$\begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|}
\hline
\text{} & \text{Sample Size} & \text{Mean} & \text{Variance} \\
\hline
\text{Data Set I} & 10 & 2 & 2 \\
\hline
\text{Data Set II} & k & 3 & 1 \\
\hline
\end{array}$$

If the variance of the pooled data set formed by combining these two data sets equals $\frac{17}{9}$, determine the value of $k$.
